cs.PL, cs.DB, cs.SE, cs.LG, cs.IR 

The paper discusses a library that integrates external structured data into F# using type providers, which is a programming language feature related to programming languages and software engineering (cs.PL). The library also includes a shape inference algorithm that infers a shape from representative sample documents, which is related to databases (cs.DB). The paper also mentions additional safety guarantees, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE). The library's integration with the F# type system and the formalization of the process and proof of a relative type soundness theorem are related to machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
